es]]||&nbsp;||19 March 1314||1322||&nbsp;\n|-\n||29||[[Jo\u00e3o II Gomes]]||&nbsp;||25 March 1323||5 December 1327||5 December 1327\n|-\n||30||[[Vasco Martins (bishop)|Vasco Martins]]<ref>Vasco Martins was a nephew of Bishop Giraldo. He was born in Medello (diocese of Lamego). Fl\u00f3rez, pp. 127-131.</ref>||&nbsp;||15 January 1328||25 September 1342<ref>Valascus Martinez was transferred to the diocese of Lisbon on 25 September 1346 by Pope Clement VI. Eubel, I, p. 406, 506.</ref>||&nbsp;\n|-\n||31||[[Pedro Afonso (bishop)|Pedro Alfonso]]<ref>Pedro Alfonso was the nephew of Archbishop Gonzalo Pereyra of Braga. Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 131-136.</ref>||&nbsp;||25 September 1342<ref>Petrus Alfonso was transferred from the diocese of Astorga by [[Pope Clement VI]] on 25 September 1342. Eubel, I, p. 406.</ref>||1357||1358 ?&nbsp;\n|-\n||32||[[Afonso Pires]]||&nbsp;||1357||6 September 1372||6 September 1372\n|-\n||33||[[Louren\u00e7o Vicente]]<ref>Vicente was only bishop-elect. He was nominated by the King, but did not receive papal confirmation for the diocese of Porto. Instead he was named to the diocese of Braga. Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 142-144.</ref>||&nbsp;||27 March 1373||6 November 1373<ref>He was appointed Archbishop of Braga by [[Pope Gregory XI]] on 19 December 1373. Eubel, I, p. 144.</ref>||&nbsp;\n|-\n||34||[[Jo\u00e3o III (bishop of Porto)|Jo\u00e3o III]]<ref>Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 144-148.</ref>||&nbsp;||9 February 1373<ref>Bishop John was appointed by Pope Gregory XI. He was transferred by the Pope from the diocese of Silves (1365\u20131373). He had earlier been Dean of the Chapter of the Cathedral of Porto. Eubel, I, pp. 406, 452.</ref>||c. 1388||c. 1388\n|-\n||35||[[Martinho Gil (bishop of Porto, 1390)|Martinho Gil]]||&nbsp;||4 June 1390<ref>Eubel, I, p. 406.</ref>||15 February 1391<ref>Bishop Martinho Gil was transferred to the diocese of Silves on 15 February 1391 by [[Pope Boniface IX]