atin|pages=782\u2013790, at p. 788\u2013789}} Eubel, I, p. 406.</ref>||30 June 1309<ref>Capelier died on 30 June 1309. Alban\u00e9s, p. 789.</ref>||30 June 1309<ref>Fredolus died in Avignon: Fl\u00f3rez, p. 303.</ref>&nbsp;\n|-\n||27|| [[Fr. Stephanus]], O. Min.<ref>Friar Stephan, [[Frei Est\u00eav\u00e3o]], a Franciscan, Confessor of [[Denis of Portugal|King Diniz of Portugal]].</ref>||&nbsp;||11 February 1310<ref>Fl\u00f3rez, pp. 114-119. Eubel, I, p. 406. His bull of appointment by [[Pope Clement V]] is printed by Fl\u00f3rez, pp. 303-304.</ref>||8 October 1313<ref>Fr. Stephanus was named Bishop of Lisbon by Pope Clement V on 8 October 1313. He was transferred to the diocese of Cuenca on 21 August 1322 by [[Pope John XXII]]. Eubel, I, p. 200, 506.</ref>|| 28 March 1326<ref>Gams, p. 31, column 1.</ref>\n|-\n||28||[[Fernando II Ramires]]||&nbsp;||19 March 1314||1322||&nbsp;\n|-\n||29||[[Jo\u00e3o II Gomes]]||&nbsp;||25 March 1323||5 December 1327||5 December 1327\n|-\n||30||[[Vasco Martins (bishop)|Vasco Martins]]<ref>Vasco Martins was a nephew of Bishop Giraldo. He was born in Medello (diocese of Lamego). Fl\u00f3rez, pp. 127-131.</ref>||&nbsp;||15 January 1328||25 September 1342<ref>Valascus Martinez was transferred to the diocese of Lisbon on 25 September 1346 by Pope Clement VI. Eubel, I, p. 406, 506.</ref>||&nbsp;\n|-\n||31||[[Pedro Afonso (bishop)|Pedro Alfonso]]<ref>Pedro Alfonso was the nephew of Archbishop Gonzalo Pereyra of Braga. Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 131-136.</ref>||&nbsp;||25 September 1342<ref>Petrus Alfonso was transferred from the diocese of Astorga by [[Pope Clement VI]] on 25 September 1342. Eubel, I, p. 406.</ref>||1357||1358 ?&nbsp;\n|-\n||32||[[Afonso Pires]]||&nbsp;||1357||6 September 1372||6 September 1372\n|-\n||33||[[Louren\u00e7o Vicente]]<ref>Vicente was only bishop-elect. He was nominated by the King, but did not receive papal confirmation for the diocese of Porto. Instead he was named to the diocese of Braga. Fl\