a\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 166-168.</ref>||&nbsp;||24 August 1453<ref>Eubel, II, p. 218.</ref>|||26 November 1464<ref>Luis Perez was transferred to the diocese of Evora on 26 November 1464 by [[Pope Paul II]]. Eubel, II, pp. 149, 218. He was transferred to Braga in 1468.</ref>||March 1480<ref>Eubel, II, p. 110.</ref>\n|-\n||45||[[Jo\u00e3o VI de Azevedo]]||&nbsp;||1465||1494||&nbsp;\n|-\n||46||[[Diogo I de Sousa]]||&nbsp;||1494||1505||&nbsp;\n|-\n||47||[[Diogo II \u00c1lvares da Costa]]||&nbsp;||1505||1507||&nbsp;\n|-\n||48||[[Pedro VI \u00c1lvares da Costa]]||1484||12 February 1507||8 January 1535||20 February 1563\n|-\n||49||[[Belchior Beliago]]||&nbsp;||1535||1538||&nbsp;\n|-\n||50||[[Baltazar Limpo]]||&nbsp;||1538||1552||&nbsp;\n|-\n||51||[[Rodrigo I Pinheiro]]||&nbsp;||1552||1574||&nbsp;\n|-\n||52||[[Aires da Silva]]||&nbsp;||1574||4 August 1578||4 August 1578\n|-\n||53||[[Sim\u00e3o de S\u00e1 Pereira (bishop)]]<ref>Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 195-197.</ref>||&nbsp;||13 November 1579<ref>Simon de Sa had been Bishop of Lamego from 1575 to 1579. Eubel, III, pp. 218, 278.</ref>||&nbsp;||March 1581&nbsp;\n|-\n||54||[[Marcos de Lisboa]], O.Min.<ref>Marcos de Betania was born in Lisbon: Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 197-202.</ref>||&nbsp;||20 October 1581<ref>Eubel, III, p. 278.</ref>||13 September 1591||13 September 1591&nbsp;\n|-\n||55||[[Jer\u00f3nimo I de Menezes]]<ref>Born in Santar\u00e9n, he was the son of Don Henrique de Menezes, Governor of Tanger. He was a doctor of theology from Coimbra, and he became Rector of the University. He had been Bishop of Miranda from 1579 to 1592. Eubel, III, p. 246. Fl\u00f3rez, ''Espa\u00f1a Sagrada'' XXI, pp. 202-204.</ref>||&nbsp;||22 May 1592<ref>He was nominated by King Philip II. Gauchat, IV, p. 286.</ref>||12 December 1600||12 December 1600<ref>Menezes died in Lisbon on 12 December 1600. Almeida, p. 876.</ref>&nbsp;\n|-\n||56||[[Gon\u00e7alo de Morais]]. O.S.B.<ref>Gon\u00e7alo de Mora